8.4 Access Modifiers

* Types:
The four access modifiers are
public, protected, default (no modifier), and private.

1. Public: The public modifier allows access from any other class.
           For classes, it means they can be accessed from any other package.

2. Protected: The protected modifier allows access within the same package and subclasses.

3. Default: If no access modifier is specified, it's the default,
            allowing access only within the same package.

4. Private: The private modifier restricts access to the defining class only.

5. Class-Level Access: Only public and default (no modifier) access modifiers
                       are applicable for top-level classes.

6. Member-Level Access: Methods, constructors, and variables can use
                         all four access modifiers to control visibility.

